import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='Miles_per_Gallon', kde=True, color='blue', bins=20)
    median_mpg = data['Miles_per_Gallon'].median()
    plt.axvline(median_mpg, color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Median: {median_mpg:.2f}')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of Miles_per_Gallon?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Year'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['Year'])]
    data['Year'] = data['Year'].dt.year

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='Year', y='Miles_per_Gallon', data=data, ci=None)
    plt.title('How has the Miles_per_Gallon changed over the years?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Miles_per_Gallon')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
